==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emasculate
<hw>E*mas"cu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Emasculated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Emasculating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>emasculare</ets>; <ets>e</ets> + <ets>masculus</ets> male,
masculine. See <er>Male</er> masculine.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
deprive of virile or procreative power; to castrate power; to castrate;
to geld.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of masculine vigor or spirit; to weaken;
to render effeminate; to vitiate by unmanly softness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Luxury had not <qex>emasculated</qex> their minds.</q> <rj><qau>V.
Knox.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>emasculate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: emasculate
<hw>e*mas"cu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Deprived of
virility or vigor; unmanned; weak.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Emasculate</xex>
slave.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>emasculated</ent>⟦br⟧
